article.description: — Tylor Perry had a season-high 25 points as North Texas topped Middle Tennessee 70-63 on Saturday.
article.headline: Perry carries North Texas past Middle Tennessee 70-63
article.linkText: Perry carries North Texas past Middle Tennessee 70-63
article.story: DENTON, Texas -- — Tylor Perry had a season-high 25 points as North Texas topped Middle Tennessee 70-63 on Saturday. Perry hit 4 of 6 3-pointers. Mardrez McBride had 11 points for North Texas (9-4, 2-1 Conference USA). Rubin Jones added 10 points and six rebounds. Thomas Bell had three blocks. Josh Jefferson had 19 points for the Blue Raiders (9-6, 0-2). Donovan Sims added 12 points and seven rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
